    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear focal point. With a stellar score of 82.07, he faces a favorable matchup against Petty (6.57 xERA), and his elite speed\u2014our primary scarcity target\u2014positions him to capitalize on the weak opposing arm. **Junior Caminero** (65.79) and **Trea Turner** (65.20) round out our top-tier plays. **Trea Turner** is particularly vital today, as his leadoff spot against Junk provides a 10% efficiency bump, ensuring he remains our most reliable engine for Runs and SB production. We also expect strong offensive contributions from **Yordan Alvarez** (63.86) and **Carson Benge** (63.27), the latter of whom benefits significantly from a +14% park factor that elevates his utility despite a lower-middle-order assignment.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Caleb Durbin**; while his base projection is solid, his status as a non-starter in today's official lineup rendered him ineligible for the active roster. We are currently monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (41.69) and **Colt Keith** (42.94), who sit near the threshold of our floor. **Hyeseong Kim** remains in the lineup primarily due to the \"Slow SP Delivery\" bonus, which increases his stolen base potential despite an unfavorable platoon disadvantage against Okert. Conversely, we are keeping a close watch on **Kazuma Okamoto** (58.18); while he performs well, his output is hampered by a -6% park factor. We continue to hold **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, and **Lars Nootbaar** in reserve due to their ongoing IL or minor league assignments, leaving our depth options like **Gary Sanchez**, **Josh Smith**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** as strictly situational depth should any of our starters be pulled mid-game.",
